# Load expression data from a CSV file
auto_mono <- as.matrix(read.csv("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/log2normalized_counts_allconds.txt", sep = ""))
autologous <- as.matrix(read.csv("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/autologous_log2normalized_counts.txt", sep = ""))
monoculture <- as.matrix(read.csv("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/monoculture_log2normalized_counts.txt", sep = ""))

# Load gene sets from a GMT file
# https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb/human/
# H Collection: Hallmark gene sets, representing well-defined biological states or processes.
# C2 Collection: Curated gene sets, including canonical pathways (KEGG, Reactome).
# C5 Collection: Gene Ontology gene sets for biological processes, molecular functions, and cellular components.
gene_sets_c2 <- getGmt("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/c2.all.v2024.1.Hs.symbols.gmt")
gene_sets_c5 <- getGmt("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/c5.all.v2024.1.Hs.symbols.gmt")
gene_sets_hallmarks <- getGmt("/home/hugo.chenel/Downloads/h.all.v2024.1.Hs.symbols.gmt")

# Perform GSVA

Annotation

# Extracting 'Day' and 'Culture' from column names
column_info <- str_split(colnames(gsva_results_automono_hallmarks), "_", simplify = TRUE)
Day <- column_info[, 1]      # Extract Day (e.g., "D1")
Patient <- column_info[, 2]      # Extract Day (e.g., "D1")
Culture <- column_info[, 4]  # Extract Culture type (e.g., "auto", "mono")

# Create annotation data frame
annotation_col <- data.frame(
  Day = factor(Day, levels = c("D1", "D4", "D8", "D11", "D14")),
  Patient = factor(Patient, levels = c("p1", "p2", "p3")),
  Culture = factor(Culture, levels = c("auto", "B"))
)
rownames(annotation_col) <- colnames(gsva_results_automono_hallmarks)

# Define annotation colors
annotation_colors <- list(
  Day = c(
    "D1"  = "#1f78b4",  # Blue
    "D4"  = "#33a02c",  # Green
    "D8"  = "#e31a1c",  # Red
    "D11" = "#ff7f00",  # Orange
    "D14" = "#6a3d9a"   # Purple
  ),
  Patient = c(
    "p1" = "#a6cee3",  # Light Blue
    "p2" = "#1f78b4",  # Blue
    "p3" = "#b2df8a"   # Light Green
  ),
  Culture = c(
    "auto" = "#b2df8a",  # Light Green
    "B" = "#fb9a99"   # Light Red
  )
)

Basic heatmaps

# Define the color palette
hmcol <- colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(10, "RdBu")))(256)

# Generate basic heatmap
pheatmap(
  gsva_results_automono_hallmarks,             # GSVA results matrix
  color = hmcol,                 # Color scheme
  scale = "row",                 # Row-wise scaling
  cluster_cols = FALSE,          # Disable column clustering
  cluster_rows = TRUE,           # Enable row clustering
  main = "GSVA heatmap for autologous and monoculture",  # Add a descriptive title
  border_color = NA,             # Remove cell borders for a cleaner look
  fontsize_row = 8,              # Adjust row label size
  fontsize_col = 8,              # Adjust column label size
)

# Generate advanced heatmap
pheatmap(
  gsva_results_automono_hallmarks,             # GSVA results matrix
  color = hmcol,                 # Color scheme
  scale = "row",                 # Row-wise scaling
  cluster_cols = TRUE,          # Disable column clustering
  cluster_rows = TRUE,           # Enable row clustering
  main = "GSVA heatmap for autologous and monoculture",  # Add a descriptive title
  fontsize_row = 8,              # Adjust row label size
  fontsize_col = 8,              # Adjust column label size
  border_color = NA,              # Remove cell borders for a cleaner look
  annotation_col = annotation_col,         # Add column annotations
  annotation_colors = annotation_colors,   # Define annotation colors
  annotation_legend = TRUE                # Show annotation legends
)

Heatmaps separated by patient

# Step 1: Identify columns corresponding to patient
selected_cols_p1 <- rownames(annotation_col)[annotation_col$Patient == "p1"]
selected_cols_p2 <- rownames(annotation_col)[annotation_col$Patient == "p2"]
selected_cols_p3 <- rownames(annotation_col)[annotation_col$Patient == "p3"]

# Step 2: Subset the GSVA results matrix to include only "px" samples
gsva_p1 <- gsva_results_automono_hallmarks[, selected_cols_p1]
gsva_p2 <- gsva_results_automono_hallmarks[, selected_cols_p2]
gsva_p3 <- gsva_results_automono_hallmarks[, selected_cols_p3]

# Step 3: Subset the annotations to include only "p1" samples

annotation_p2 <- annotation_col[selected_cols_p2, ]
annotation_p3 <- annotation_col[selected_cols_p3, ]
